  <part id="design">
    <title>Design</title>

    <slide id="what-is-api-design">
      <title>What is API Design?</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Definition</li>
        <li>Rationale</li>
        <li>Guide</li>
        <li>Reference</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="first-why-design-apis">
      <title>First, Why Design APIs?</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Every API starts with a story</li>
        <ul>
          <li>&quot;We need ...&quot;</li>
          <li>&quot;Our customers want ...&quot;</li>
          <li>&quot;I have an idea ...&quot;</li>
        </ul>
        <li>Designing is critical to success</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="what-is-api-design-definition">
      <title>What is API Design : Definition</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Creating a design sets boundaries</li>
        <li>Establishes target audience</li>
        <li>Identifies measures of success</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="what-is-api-design-rationale">
      <title>What is API Design : Rationale</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Creates a reason for this API</li>
        <li>Shows the set of actions</li>
        <li>Details results</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="what-is-api-design-guide">
      <title>What is API Design : Guide</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Offers hints for properites and resources</li>
        <li>Helps programmers say 'yes' or 'no'</li>
        <li>Encourages paying attention to measures</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="what-is-api-design-reference">
      <title>What is API Design : Reference</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Provides examples for API users</li>
        <li>Responds to common challenges</li>
        <li>Invites alternate uses</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="what-is-api-design-summary">
      <title>What is API Design : Summary</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Defines your API</li>
        <li>Gives meaning/purpose to your work</li>
        <li>Acts as a guide while building</li>
        <li>Provides a reference for users</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
  </part>
  
  <part id="api-stories">
    <title>API Stories</title>

    <slide id="api-stories">
      <title>API Stories</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Design process guidance</li>
        <li>Shared understanding (across teams)</li>
        <li>Structured MD document</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-example">
      <title>API Story Example</title>
      <img 
          src="mamund-design-story.png" 
          title="Task Management API Story" 
          href="https://github.com/mamund/2025-05-ai-apis-design-with-alps/blob/main/01-api-stories-to-alps/tasks-api-story.md" 
          class="fullsize"/>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-elements">
      <title>API Story Elements</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Purpose</li>
          <ul>
            <li>Simple statement</li>
          </ul>
        <li>Properties</li>
          <ul>
            <li>All the data points (storage and queries)</li>
          </ul>
        <li>Resources</li>
          <ul>
            <li>RESTful states (home, list, item, etc.)</li>
          </ul>        
        <li>Actions</li>
          <ul>
            <li>list, read, write, update, delete, share, etc.</li>
          </ul>
        <li>Rules</li>
          <ul>
            <li>limits, validators, etc.</li>
          </ul>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-purpose">
      <title>API Story : Purpose</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Simple statement</li>
        <li>Shareable</li>
        <li>Repeatable</li>
        <li>Sets scope and audience</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-purpose-example">
      <title>API Story : Purpose : Example</title>
      <img 
          src="mamund-design-purpose.png" 
          title="Task Management API Purpose" 
          href="https://github.com/mamund/2025-05-ai-apis-design-with-alps/blob/main/01-api-stories-to-alps/tasks-api-story.md" 
          class="fullsize"/>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-properties">
      <title>API Story : Properties</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Data points for the API</li>
        <li>Includes storage and query properties</li>
        <li>Provides clear list and definition</li>
        <li>Chance to reuse shared properties</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-properties-example">
      <title>API Story : Properties : Example</title>
      <img 
          src="mamund-design-properties.png" 
          title="Task Management API Properties" 
          href="https://github.com/mamund/2025-05-ai-apis-design-with-alps/blob/main/01-api-stories-to-alps/tasks-api-story.md" 
          class="fullsize"/>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-resources">
      <title>API Story : Resources</title>
      <ul>
        <li>&quot;Resting places&quot; for your API</li>
        <li>Typically organized as HOME, COLLECTION, ITEM</li>
        <li>Each resource is a 'state'</li>
        <li>States return both properites and actions</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-resources-example">
      <title>API Story : Resources : Example</title>
      <img 
          src="mamund-design-resources.png" 
          title="Task Management API Resources" 
          href="https://github.com/mamund/2025-05-ai-apis-design-with-alps/blob/main/01-api-stories-to-alps/tasks-api-story.md" 
          class="fullsize"/>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-actions">
      <title>API Story : Actions</title>
      <ul>
        <li>The things clients can *do* at each resource</li>
        <li>CRUD actions</li>
        <li>Filters</li>
        <li>Custom Actions (e.g. markComplete)</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-actions-example">
      <title>API Story : Actions : Example</title>
      <img 
          src="mamund-design-actions.png" 
          title="Task Management API Actions" 
          href="https://github.com/mamund/2025-05-ai-apis-design-with-alps/blob/main/01-api-stories-to-alps/tasks-api-story.md" 
          class="fullsize"/>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-rules">
      <title>API Story : Rules</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Limits on some actions</li>
        <li>Usually implemented behind the interface</li>
        <li>Examples:</li>
        <li>ID must be unique</li>
        <li>Customers cannot have duplicate accounts</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-rules-example">
      <title>API Story : Rules : Example</title>
      <img 
          src="mamund-design-rules.png" 
          title="Task Management API Rules" 
          href="https://github.com/mamund/2025-05-ai-apis-design-with-alps/blob/main/01-api-stories-to-alps/tasks-api-story.md" 
          class="fullsize"/>
    </slide>
    <slide id="api-story-summary">
      <title>API Story : Summary</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Structured markdown</li>
        <li>Purpose, Properties, Resources, Actions, Rules</li>
        <li>Design guidance, shared understanding</li>
      </ul>
    </slide>
